summary: ON 12/19/2018, AT APPROXIMATELY 1630, I WAS DRIVING ON I-76N; 60 MPH  THE HOOD OF MY CAR FLEW UP, CRASHING INTO THE WINDSHIELD.  FORTUNATELY, I WAS IN THE LH LANE AND WAS ABLE TO COAST TO THE MEDIAN.  MY WINDSHIELD WAS CRACKED. THE FORCE OF THE HIT WAS SO STRONG IT KNOCKED OFF THE REAR VIEW MIRROR.  DAMAGE: HOOD, WINDSHIELD AND ROOF  CAR WAS TOTALED
